Durban - A 4-year-old girl was burnt to death as she lay asleep on her grandmother’s bed in a corrugated iron shack in Verulam on Saturday night.
Melokuhle Mkhize was left in the care of her grandmother Nokuthula Ndlovu, by her 19-year-old mother, Nondumiso Mkhize, who was busy with her Grade 11 exams.

When The Mercury arrived at the family home, Ndlovu had been picked up by the police and taken to the police station for questioning.
The circumstances surrounding who lit the candle that started the fire are still unclear.
Sabelo Mbuyisa, 10, said he was sitting outside with his brother, Sibusiso, 7, when the fire started after 10pm.

He said his mother had left and the candle inside the house “got finished”, which caused the newspaper it was on to catch alight.
“I ran inside and tried to pull my sister (niece) out, but the blanket was stuck to the bed. My brother and I got burnt. I grabbed my brother and ran outside,” said Sabelo.
Sabelo said the fire started at the foot of the bed because Melokuhle’s legs were burnt.

 







